<body id="encoder___installation">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">Encoder - Installation</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Installation of the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">In order to fix the new assembly to the center <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em>, mount the support for the center
                            <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> and the two-parted washer
                    on the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> assembly (marked with "A" and
                    "B" in <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___removal.html#encoder___removal__Center_waveguide">Figure 4</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Push the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> assembly up against the
                    center <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> and guide the two parts of
                    the washer, until they fit the two grooves in the center <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount and tighten the four washers and four nuts (marked with red arrows in <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___removal.html#encoder___removal__Bolts_fixing_the_assy">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                <div class="itemgroup info">Tightening torque 1.8 Nm.</div>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the flexible <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> and the new
                    copper gasket - insert the four screws and tighten them.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Guide the flexible <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> into the
                    cut-away in the plate and turn the plate clockwise to vertical position.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the support plate on the four nuts (marked with green arrows in <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___removal.html#encoder___removal__Bolts_fixing_the_assy">Figure 2</a>)
                    and pull the support plate away from the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> assembly. Tighten the nuts.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the four hexagon bolts (marked with red arrows in <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___removal.html#encoder___removal__Bolts_fixing_the_assy">Figure 2</a>)
                    and tighten them.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the single hexagon bolt (marked with an orange arrow in <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___removal.html#encoder___removal__Bolts_fixing_the_assy">Figure 2</a>)
                    and tighten it.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Make the connection between the fixed <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> and the flexible <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> on the
                            <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> assembly. Mount the four <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Waveguide</span></em> screws and tighten them.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> cover or release it from
                    horizontal position.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Connect the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Encoder</span></em> cable in the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Junction Box</span></em> through the stuffing tube.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Close the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Junction Box</span></em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Close the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Motor Cover</span></em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Do the necessary adjustments in the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Transceiver</span></em> (see <a class="xref" href="cm_encoder___north_alignment.html#cm_encoder___north_alignment" title="North alignment of the Transceiver.">Encoder - North alignment</a>).</span>
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

</body>
